Package valworkbench.exceptions

Exception Summary
DirNotFoundException Signals that an attempt to open the directory denoted by a specified path name, has failed because the directory not exist.
EmptyDirException Signals that the directory denoted by a specified pathname is empty
EmptyListException Signals that the list is empty
ErrorAlgorithmException Signals that the execution of the specified algorithm has failed
FileAlgNotFoundException Signals that an attempt to open the executable file denoted by a specified path name has failed
InvalidCmndLineException Signals that an invalid command line has been entered
InvalidDirectoryException Signals that an attempt to open the directory denoted by a specified path name, has failed because the directory contains old experiment data
NotEnoughArgException Signals that not enough arguments has been entered
NotValidFormatException Signals that the file opened have an invalid format
NotValidOptionException Signals that an invalid option has been selected
PermissionDeniedException Signals that an attempt to open the directory denoted by a specified path name, has failed because the directory contains old experiment data
TerminateExecutionException Signals that an invalid option has been selected
